SIMPLE: parlous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parlous
<hw>Par"lous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[For
<ets>perlous</ets>, a contr. fr. <ets>perilous</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Attended with peril; dangerous; <as>as, a
<ex>parlous</ex> cough</as>. </def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>parlous</xex> snuffing.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Venturesome; bold; mischievous; keen.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>parlous</xex> boy.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Shak.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>parlous</xex> wit.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Dryden.</au>
-- <wordforms><wf>Par"lous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
-- <wf>Par"lous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parmelia</ent>⟦br⟧
